### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

With `*ngIf` we could do:
```html
<div *ngIf="a; else empty">Value A</div>
<div *ngIf="b; else empty">Value B</div>
<div *ngIf="c; else empty">Value C</div>
<ng-template #empty>
  <div>Empty</div>
</ng-template>
```
And it is very handy when all conditionals have the same else block.

With the new control flow the best we can do is:
```html
@if (a) {
  <div>Value A</div>
} @else {
  <ng-container *ngTemplateOutlet="empty"></ng-container>
}
@if (b) {
  <div>Value B</div>
} @else {
  <ng-container *ngTemplateOutlet="empty"></ng-container>
}
@if (c) {
  <div>Value C</div>
} @else {
  <ng-container *ngTemplateOutlet="empty"></ng-container>
}
<ng-template #empty>
  <div>Empty</div>
</ng-template>
```
Which is much more verbose.

### Proposed solution

Allowing for a less verbose way to specify reusable template as `@else`.
For example:
```html
@if (a) {
  <div>Value</div>
} @else empty
```
Or:
```html
@if (a) {
  <div>Value</div>
} @else #empty
```

### Alternatives considered

Using `<ng-container *ngTemplateOutlet="empty"></ng-container>` in every `@else` block

